### Delete Session Cookie in Next.js App Router

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/authentication.mdx

This function deletes the 'session' cookie using Next.js `cookies()` from `next/headers`. It ensures server-side execution and is suitable for logout flows or session invalidation.

```ts
import 'server-only'
import { cookies } from 'next/headers'

export async function deleteSession() {
  const cookieStore = await cookies()
  cookieStore.delete('session')
}
```

