### Set Cookies Using Set-Cookie Header in Next.js Response

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/03-file-conventions/route.mdx

Shows how to return cookies by setting the Set-Cookie header in the Response object. Retrieves a token from the cookie store and includes it in the response headers. This approach provides an alternative to the cookies() function for setting cookies in API routes.

```typescript
import { cookies } from 'next/headers'

export async function GET(request: Request) {
  const cookieStore = await cookies()
  const token = cookieStore.get('token')

  return new Response('Hello, Next.js!', {
    status: 200,
    headers: { 'Set-Cookie': `token=${token.value}` },
  })
}
```

